- `integration-plan.md`
- `decision-log.md`
- `runlog.md`
- `incidents.md`
- `lessons.md`
- `tasks/`
- `reports/`
- `logs/`
- `locks/`

## Worktree Planning

Generate suggested branch/worktree commands:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/plan_worktrees.py \
  --mission "mission title" \
  --task A1=backend-api \
  --task A2=frontend-ui \
  --task A3=tests
```

Review generated commands before running them. They are printed, not executed.

## Worker Launch

Print worker launch commands:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/launch_commands.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder> \
  --agent codex \
  --task A1=../Fusion_crm-A1 \
  --task A2=../Fusion_crm-A2
```

Launch a wave unattended:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/run_wave.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder> \
  --agent codex \
  --mode background \
  --task A1=../Fusion_crm-A1 \
  --task A2=../Fusion_crm-A2
```

Use `--agent claude` for Claude Code workers. Use `--mode tmux` for visible tmux sessions.

Check status:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/status_wave.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder> \
  --tail 20
```

Check ownership for a task:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/check_ownership.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder> \
  --task A1 \
  --base main
```

## Context Handoff

Generate a compact handoff after waves, before integration, before release gates, or at end of day:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/summarize_mission.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder>
```

Record a workflow incident:

```bash
python3 .agents/skills/agent-orchestrator/scripts/record_incident.py \
  --mission-folder .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder> \
  --title "Worker used wrong worktree" \
  --area launch \
  --severity medium \
  --what-happened "A1 launched in the primary repo instead of its worktree." \
  --impact "Worker could have touched unowned files." \
  --root-cause "Launch command was copied without --cd worktree." \
  --immediate-fix "Stopped worker and relaunched with run_wave.py." \
  --lesson-candidate "Always launch workers through run_wave.py or generated commands." \
  --follow-up "Check launch command in every Wave plan."
```

Resume prompt:

```text
Use the orchestrator protocol in .agents/orchestrator/PROTOCOL.md.

Resume mission from .agents/orchestration/<mission-folder>.
Read handoff.md first, then inspect backlog.md, daily-sprint.md, goal.md, acceptance.md, verification.md, linear-sync.md, contract.md, ownership.md, ownership.yaml, board.md, integration-plan.md, decision-log.md, runlog.md, incidents.md, lessons.md, runtime.json, and reports needed for the next decision. Evaluate goal.md and acceptance.md, summarize current state, identify blockers, sync Linear if needed, apply accepted lessons, and prepare the next wave or integration plan. Do not implement feature work unless explicitly asked.
```

## Templates

Prefer shared templates from `.agents/orchestrator/templates/`.
Use worker role profiles from `.agents/orchestrator/worker-types/`.

